---
description: graphify knowledge graph — agent routines (Consultant + Cline)
alwaysApply: true
---

Local graph at graphify-out/ (gitignored). Regenerate: py -3.12 -m graphify update .

## Consultant / Otto (read-only)

- When graphify-out/graph.json exists, before broad repo search:
  py -3.12 -m graphify query "<narrow question>"
  py -3.12 -m graphify path "<A>" "<B>"
  py -3.12 -m graphify explain "<node>"
- Narrow queries (e.g. site/progress.js export import). Prefer path/explain when paths are known.
- Never read graph.json into context.
- GRAPH_REPORT.md: read only ## God Nodes, ## Surprising Connections, ## Suggested Questions, and the short header (Corpus/Summary/Freshness). Skip ## Community Hubs and ## Communities entirely.
- Do not run graphify update.
- May run `python3 scripts/check_graphify_freshness.py` (no `--strict`) to
  report staleness; must not run `graphify update`.

## Cline (implementer)

- After edits under `site/` or `phases/`:
  1. `py -3.12 -m graphify update .`
  2. `python3 scripts/check_graphify_freshness.py --strict` (must exit 0)
- If the session only changed README, ROADMAP, glossary, or quiz.json (no
  `phases/**/code/` and no `site/`), skip both steps unless the user asks.
- Use query/path/explain when reviewing PRs.

## Do not

- Run graphify site on the only graph (replaces full curriculum graph with site-only).
- Commit graphify-out/.
- Use Obsidian or --wiki for this project unless user explicitly requests later.
- Do not add CI, pre-commit hooks, or commit `graphify-out/` for freshness.
